---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer"
  description="Disclaimer for Dev Error DB troubleshooting content, source-backed labels, general guidance, and production safety."
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
    <p>
      Dev Error DB provides developer troubleshooting information for
      educational and diagnostic use. The site helps narrow possible causes and
      checks for error messages, but it cannot guarantee that any fix applies to
      every environment.
    </p>
    <h2>Source-backed does not mean guaranteed</h2>
    <p>
      A source-backed page means the page includes public or otherwise safe
      references used to understand the error pattern. It does not mean the
      underlying issue is still open, that a vendor has endorsed this site, or
      that the same fix will work for your project.
    </p>
    <h2>Production safety</h2>
    <p>
      Before changing production systems, capture non-secret diagnostics, test
      the smallest change in a safe environment, keep a rollback path, and avoid
      exposing credentials in logs, tickets, screenshots, or support requests.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
